Note:
F# Lexer - Complete tokenization for F# functional programming language

This file provides comprehensive lexical analysis for the F# programming
language, covering both functional programming constructs and .NET integration.

Every token produced by this lexer is a 40-byte token record carrying the
token type, the lexeme string (cooked for string/char literals: escape
sequences are decoded at tokenization time), the numeric payload (parsed
integer value or IEEE-754 float bits for numeric literals, the code point
for char literals), and the source line/column. The parser stores these
token records in AST value slots so the HIR translator can recover
identifier names and literal payloads without re-lexing.

F# Features Covered:
- Keywords (let, match, with, function, type, module, open, etc.)
- Functional operators (|>, <|, >>, <<, composition, piping)
- Pattern matching syntax (|, when, wildcard patterns)
- Type annotations and signatures (: type, -> arrow types)
- Computation expressions (async, seq, query workflows)
- .NET interop (member, interface, inherit, override)
- Quotations and code generation (<@ @>)
- Record types, discriminated unions, tuples
- Comments (line, block with nesting, XML documentation)
- String literals (regular with escapes, verbatim, triple-quoted, byte)
- Numeric literals in all bases with type suffixes

Dependencies:
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa
- compiler/internal/string_utils.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils

