@Reasoning:
F# char literal: 'X' or '\X' (single character, possibly escaped,
delimited by single quotes). The token's numeric payload carries the
decoded code point and the lexeme carries the cooked UTF-8 bytes of the
character. Escape decoding covers the simple escapes plus \xHH and
\uXXXX. Unterminated or malformed char literals return TOKEN_ERROR.
@End Reasoning
Process called "read_char_literal" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Lex an F# character literal into a token with decoded code point payload

    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 0
    Let line be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16
    Let column be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 24
    Let start_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8

    Let current be proc current_char with lexer
    If current is not equal to 39:  Note: opening single quote
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_ERROR, 0, 0, line, column
    End If

